# Validation Rules

## 📌 PURPOSE

Defines validation rules for all incoming API requests.

Ensures data integrity, security, and consistent error handling.

---

## 🚨 MANDATORY VALIDATION

### DO

* Validate all request DTOs
* Use validation annotations
* Reject invalid inputs

### DO NOT

* Do not accept unchecked input
* Do not validate in controller manually

---

## 🧾 VALIDATION ANNOTATIONS

### DO

Use standard annotations:

* `@NotNull`
* `@NotBlank`
* `@Size`
* `@Min`
* `@Max`
* `@Email` (if applicable)

---

## 🟢 REQUEST DTO VALIDATION

### DO

* Apply validation inside DTO

### EXAMPLE

```java id="val1"
public class CreateTaskRequest {

    @NotBlank(message = "Title is required")
    private String title;

    @Size(max = 255, message = "Description too long")
    private String description;
}
```

---

## ⚙️ CONTROLLER VALIDATION

### DO

* Use `@Valid` in controller

### EXAMPLE

```java id="val2"
@PostMapping
public ResponseEntity<TaskResponse> create(
        @Valid @RequestBody CreateTaskRequest request) {
}
```

---

## 🔄 UPDATE VALIDATION

### DO

* Keep fields optional
* Validate only if present

### EXAMPLE

```java id="val3"
public class UpdateTaskRequest {

    private String title;

    @Size(max = 255)
    private String description;
}
```

---

## ⚠️ VALIDATION FAILURE HANDLING

### DO

* Let validation errors go to global exception handler

### RESPONSE FORMAT

```java id="val4"
{
  "statusCode": 400,
  "message": "Validation failed",
  "errors": [
    {
      "field": "title",
      "message": "must not be blank"
    }
  ]
}
```

---

## 🧱 CUSTOM VALIDATION (OPTIONAL)

### DO

* Use custom validators for complex rules

### EXAMPLE

```java id="val5"
@AssertTrue(message = "Invalid state")
public boolean isValid() {
    return title != null && !title.isEmpty();
}
```

---

## 🚫 DO NOT RULES

* Do not validate inside service unless business logic
* Do not skip validation
* Do not return raw validation errors
* Do not expose internal messages

---

## ⚙️ BEST PRACTICES

### DO

* Keep validation simple
* Add clear error messages
* Validate early (DTO level)

---

## 🧪 TDD RULES

### DO

* Write tests for validation failures

### EXAMPLE

```java id="val6"
@Test
void shouldFailWhenTitleIsBlank() throws Exception {
    mockMvc.perform(post("/v1/tasks")
        .content("{\"title\":\"\"}")
        .contentType("application/json"))
        .andExpect(status().isBadRequest());
}
```

---

## 🧠 AI ENFORCEMENT RULES

* MUST validate all request DTOs
* MUST use validation annotations
* MUST use @Valid in controller
* MUST NOT accept invalid input
* MUST return structured validation errors

